<h2>Manage associated work items</h2>

<p>Associated work items are tangible outputs or outcomes that a work item produces. Managing associated work items helps track what the work is delivering and when.</p>

<h3>Viewing associated work items</h3>
<p>To view associated work items:</p>
<ol>
    <li>Navigate to your work item's detail page</li>
    <li>Go to the <strong>Products</strong> tab</li>
    <li>View the associated work items table</li>
</ol>

<h3>Associated work item information</h3>
<p>Each associated work item shows:</p>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Name:</strong> Associated work item title</li>
    <li><strong>Description:</strong> What the associated work item is</li>
    <li><strong>Status:</strong> Current work item status</li>
    <li><strong>Due Date:</strong> When it should be delivered</li>
    <li><strong>Actual Date:</strong> When it was actually delivered</li>
    <li><strong>Owner:</strong> Who is responsible</li>
</ul>

<h3>Adding associated work items</h3>
<p>To add a new associated work item:</p>
<ol>
    <li>Go to the <strong>Products</strong> tab</li>
    <li>Click <strong>Add Associated Work Item</strong></li>
    <li>Fill in the associated work item details:
        <ul>
            <li>Name and description</li>
            <li>Due date</li>
            <li>Owner</li>
            <li>Status</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li>Click <strong>Create</strong></li>
</ol>

<h3>Editing associated work items</h3>
<p>To update an associated work item:</p>
<ol>
    <li>Click on the associated work item name in the table</li>
    <li>Click <strong>Edit</strong></li>
    <li>Update the information</li>
    <li>Save your changes</li>
</ol>

<h3>Associated work item status</h3>
<p>Common associated work item statuses include:</p>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Planned:</strong> Associated work item is planned but not started</li>
    <li><strong>In Progress:</strong> Work has begun</li>
    <li><strong>Completed:</strong> Associated work item is finished</li>
    <li><strong>Blocked:</strong> Work is blocked by dependencies</li>
    <li><strong>Cancelled:</strong> Associated work item is no longer required</li>
</ul>

<h3>Linking to products</h3>
<p>Associated work items can be linked to products in the operational reporting system. This allows you to:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Track operational metrics for associated work items</li>
    <li>Link work item delivery to product performance</li>
    <li>Generate reports that span work and product data</li>
</ul>

<h3>Best practices</h3>
<ul>
    <li>Define associated work items clearly and specifically</li>
    <li>Set realistic due dates</li>
    <li>Update status regularly as work progresses</li>
    <li>Record actual delivery dates when complete</li>
    <li>Link associated work items to milestones where relevant</li>
    <li>Keep associated work item descriptions up to date</li>
</ul>

<h3>Associated work item reports</h3>
<p>Associated work item information is used in:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Work status reports</li>
    <li>Completion tracking</li>
    <li>Stakeholder updates</li>
    <li>Portfolio reporting</li>
</ul>

